ReSharper has a refactoring option to automatically fix code like this:

```csharp
try
{
 // do something
}
finally 
{
}
```

The ReSharper refactor action will remove the entire try/finally block preserving the code inside.

Alternatively if you have code like this:

```csharp
try
{
  // do something
}
catch
{
  // handle
}
finally
{
}
```

The ReSharper refactor action will remove the `finally { }` statement preserving the try/catch.

Visual Studio does not have an equivalent quick action for this.

